Reasoning: The paper deals with efficient bug triaging procedures in collaborative software engineering projects, which falls under the scope of software engineering (cs.SE). The use of social networks to categorize bugs and the analysis of social organization in collaborative software engineering suggest that the paper could also be classified under social and information networks (cs.SI) and software development (cs.SD). The study also involves data analysis and machine learning techniques, which could place it under cryptography and security (cs.CR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
